The paper is about implementing an automatic differentiator in ACL2, which is a theorem proving system based on first-order logic. The paper focuses on the implementation details of the macro and supporting functions that automate the process of formalizing the derivative of a particular function. This involves using the ACL2 table facility to keep track of functions and their derivatives, as well as interacting with the macro that introduces inverse functions in ACL2(r). Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). However, the paper also involves software engineering aspects (cs.SE), mathematical software (cs.MS), and scientific computing (cs.SC), which make these sub-categories likely as well.
